---
// The "Signing in" panel: how editors authenticate at /admin/editor/. The wired
// live path is Token — Sveltia's built-in "Sign in with Token", which needs no
// relay and no service: editors paste a fine-grained GitHub PAT (Contents:
// Read & Write on this repo) and it's stored in their browser. Local always
// works from a dev server. `auth_methods: [token]` in config.yml keeps the login
// screen token-only (no OAuth button). Static content — the authoritative setup
// steps live in CMS_SETUP.md.
---

<section
  style="margin-top: var(--space-xl); background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: var(--space-lg);"
>
  <h2 style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 0 0 var(--space-md);">Signing in</h2>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-md); color: var(--color-muted); max-width: var(--text-width);">
    This dashboard is a read-only summary — actual editing happens in the editor
    once you sign in. On the live site you sign in with a <strong>GitHub
    token</strong> (no extra account or service); <strong>Local</strong> works
    whenever you run a dev server. See <code>CMS_SETUP.md</code> for the full
    setup of each.
  </p>

  <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);">
    Sign in with a GitHub token (live site)
  </h3>
  <ol style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-md); padding-left: 1.2rem; color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 1.9; max-width: var(--text-width);">
    <li>
      Make sure your GitHub account has write access to
      <code>jaredcosulich/harvardintech</code>.
    </li>
    <li>
      On GitHub, go to <strong>Settings → Developer settings → Fine-grained
      tokens → Generate new token</strong>. Under <strong>Repository
      access</strong> choose <strong>Only select repositories →
      jaredcosulich/harvardintech</strong>. Under <strong>Repository
      permissions</strong> set <strong>Contents → Read and write</strong>. Pick
      an expiry, then <strong>Generate token</strong> and copy it.
    </li>
    <li>
      At <code>/admin/editor/</code>, click <strong>“Sign in with Token”</strong>
      (the only button shown) and paste the token. It’s stored in your browser
      only; your edits commit straight to the repo and the site redeploys.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);">
    Local (repo owner)
  </h3>
  <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 1.9; max-width: var(--text-width);">
    Run a local dev server, open <code>/admin/editor/</code>, and choose
    <strong>“Work with Local Repository.”</strong> No account, no token — edits
    write straight to <code>src/content/</code> on disk.
  </p>
</section>
